Zenith Bank of Nigeria Says Will Sell Its Non-Banking Units, Stay in Ghana

-- B y   V i n c e n t   N w a n m a
-- 
2011-03-24T14:43:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-24/zenith-bank-of-nigeria-says-will-sell-its-non-banking-units-stay-in-ghana.html
Zenith Bank Plc (ZENITHBA) ,  Nigeria ’s biggest
lender by market value, said it applied to the country’s central
bank for an international commercial banking license and will
sell its non-banking units.  The Lagos-based lender will keep its banking units in
 Sierra Leone ,  Ghana  and Gambia, Godwin Emefiele, its chief
executive officer, said in a conference call today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Vincent Nwanma in Lagos at 
 vnwanma@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gordon Bell at 
 gbell16@bloomberg.net  